	<p class="cs709C557D"><span class="cs5E1DB61D">WEST virginia legislature</span></p><p class="cs1CE9D70E"><span class="csB0C9F1E0">2026 regular session</span></p><p class="cs1CE9D70E"><span class="csB0C9F1E0">ENGROSSED</span></p><p class="cs709C557D"><span class="csC2FEE544">Committee Substitute</span></p><p class="cs709C557D"><span class="csC2FEE544">for</span></p><p class="cs3E63B65"><span class="cs8498B7A6">House Bill 4755</span></p><p class="cs8BEF69CE"><span class="csADC6E5DB">By Delegates Ridenour, Kump, Butler, Masters, Hillenbrand, Funkhouser, Ward, Mallow, Kimble, and Martin </span></p><p class="cs8BEF69CE"><span class="cs7B75DFFE">[Originating in the Committee on the Judiciary; Reported on February 3, 2026]</span></p><p class="cs8BEF69CE"><span class="cs7B75DFFE">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="cs29F66C3F"><span class="csEF05ACC">A BILL to amend and reenact &sect;61-11-18 of the Code of West Virginia, 1931, as amended, relating to qualifying offenses for purposes of recidivism punishment; and adding aggravated vehicular homicide, driving under the influence causing serious bodily injury, and third offense driving under the influence as qualifying offenses for enhanced sentencing of a repeat offender. </span></p><p class="cs63FD752D"><span class="cs93AB6E8B">Be it enacted by the Legislature of West Virginia:</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">&nbsp;</span></p><h2 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="cs7A33E2F1">ARTICLE 11. GENERAL PROVISIONS CONCERNING CRIMES.</span></h2>
	<h4 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="csB9803513">&sect;61-11-18. Punishment for second or third offense of felony.</span></h4>
